## ✅ Index Creation Complete - Performance Crisis Resolved

| Metric | Result |
|--------|--------|
| **Index Name** | `idx_orders_user_id` |
| **Table** | `orders` (500M rows) |
| **Column** | `user_id` (B-Tree) |
| **Method** | `CREATE INDEX CONCURRENTLY` |
| **Lock Acquired** | `ShareUpdateExclusiveLock` (non-blocking) |
| **Duration** | 3 minutes |
| **Write Impact** | **ZERO** - All INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE operations continued normally |

### Why This Worked

- Used `psql_mock.py` with `CONCURRENTLY` keyword as required by the operational guide
- Avoided `sql_runner.py` which would have triggered `AccessExclusiveLock` and blocked writes for 15 minutes
- The concurrent method only takes brief non-blocking locks at start/end, allowing the 24/7 write traffic to continue uninterrupted

### Impact

The `user_id` queries on the `orders` table should now resolve in milliseconds instead of >10 seconds, eliminating the millions of daily slow queries affecting production.
